<TITLE> Bangladesh rout Oman 7-1 in Junior (Hockey) Asia Cup </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 13 (bdnews24.com) - The Bangladesh Under-21 Hockey team handed a massive 7-1 defeat to Oman in the Men's Junior Asia Cup in their second match in Hyderabad, India, Sunday. Bangladesh, who suffered a 8-0 defeat by South Korea in their opener, led the first half with 3-1 and later added another five goals in the second half. Captain Russel Mahmud Jimmy and Hasan Jubair struck two goals each while Rimon Kumar Ghosh, Krishna Kumar and Ashaduzzaman Chandan netted one goal apiece for Bangladesh. Basim Rajab scored the lone goal for Oman. Bangladesh will take on Pakistan in their last pool match Monday. 
